{{Infobox journal | title = American Indian Quarterly | cover = | editor = Lindsey Claire Smith | discipline = [[American Indian studies]] | abbreviation = Am. Indian Q. | publisher = [[University of Nebraska Press]] | country = United States | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1974-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.nebraskapress.unl.edu/product/American-Indian-Quarterly,673174.aspx | link1 = http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/american_indian_quarterly/ | link1-name = Online access at [[Project MUSE]] | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = 0095182X | OCLC = 499289594 | LCCN = 74647596 | CODEN = AIQUEW | ISSN = 0095-182X | eISSN = 1534-1828 }} The '''''American Indian Quarterly''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering studies on the [[indigenous peoples]] of North and South America. It is published by the [[University of Nebraska Press]] and was established in 1974. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Lindsey Claire Smith ([[Oklahoma State University]]).
== External links == * {{Official website|http://www.nebraskapress.unl.edu/product/American-Indian-Quarterly,673174.aspx}}
