{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}} '''Isis Anchalee''' is a Canadian [[Full-stack developer|full-stack]] engineer.
{{Infobox person | name = Isis Anchalee | image = | caption = Isis Anchalee during TechCrunch Disrupt SF 2015 | known_for = ILookLikeAnEngineer }}
==Biography== She employed by [[OneLogin]] and later [[Uber]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Isis Anchalee|url=https://twitter.com/isisAnchalee/status/889572586375438336|website=Twitter|accessdate=1 May 2018|language=en}}</ref> and the founder of the [[I Look Like an Engineer|#ilooklikeanengineer]] [[hashtag]] created in order to promote discussion of [[gender equality]] in tech after the OneLogin featured her face in an ad campaign.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/business/technology/la-fi-tn-i-look-like-an-engineer-20150804-story.html|title=Think you know what an engineer looks like? #ilooklikeanengineer says think again|last=Times|first=Los Angeles|website=latimes.com|access-date=1 November 2016}}</ref> Anchalee is also on the Advisory Board of [[Women Who Code]].
== Creation of I Look Like An Engineer == {{main|I Look Like an Engineer}}
=== Hashtag === Anchalee created #ilooklikeanengineer (an example of [[hashtag activism]]) when she received derogatory comments about her face being featured in an ad campaign for OneLogin. Anchalee feels that most people are "...well intentioned but genuinely blind to a lot of [things] that those who do not identify as male have to deal with."<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/the-coffeelicious/you-may-have-seen-my-face-on-bart-8b9561003e0f|title=You May Have Seen My Face on BART – The Coffeelicious|last=Anchalee|first=Isis|date=1 August 2015|website=Medium|access-date=1 November 2016}}</ref> One year after the launch of #ilooklikeanengineer 250,000 plus people had used the hashtag.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/startup-grind/ilooklikeanengineer-one-year-later-b599e0cae817|title=#iLookLikeAnEngineer: One Year Later – Startup Grind|last=Anchalee|first=Isis|date=3 August 2016|website=Medium|access-date=1 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sciencealert.com/the-best-tweets-from-the-ilooklikeanengineer-hashtag|title=The best tweets from the #ILookLikeAnEngineer hashtag|last=MacDonald|first=Fiona|newspaper=ScienceAlert|access-date=1 November 2016}}</ref>
== Facebook == Her Facebook account was suspended due to similarities between her given name and the terrorist group [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIS]],<ref name="Business Insider">{{cite web|last1=Kircher|first1=Madison Malone|title=A woman named Isis claims she's been blocked from signing into Facebook|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/woman-named-isis-blocked-facebook-2015-11|work=[[Business Insider]]|accessdate=14 February 2017|language=en|date=17 November 2015}}</ref><ref name="Telegraph">{{cite web|last1=Titcomb|first1=James|title=Woman named Isis has Facebook account suspended|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/facebook/12003798/Woman-named-Isis-has-Facebook-account-suspended.html|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|''The Telegraph'']]|accessdate=14 February 2017|language=en|date=18 November 2015}}</ref><ref name="The Guardian">{{cite web|last1=Hunt|first1=Elle|title='Facebook thinks I'm a terrorist': woman named Isis has account disabled|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/nov/18/facebook-thinks-im-a-terrorist-woman-named-isis-has-account-disabled|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=14 February 2017|language=English|date=18 November 2015}}</ref> but her account was later reactivated.<ref name="Unblocked">{{cite web|last1=Kircher|first1=Madison Malone|title=Facebook finally unblocked a woman named Isis from its site — but there is still a bigger issue|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/banned-from-facebook-because-of-name-2015-11|website=Business Insider|accessdate=14 February 2017|language=en|date=17 November 2017}}</ref>
